<div id="review_3025368692" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3025368692" />
    <a title="Ethan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/79606570-ethan"><img alt="Ethan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1617242228p2/79606570.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3025368692?book_show_action=true">Nov 13, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ethan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ethan" href="/user/show/79606570-ethan">Ethan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3025368692" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4701176504770431021"><i>The Aleph and Other Stories</i> collects two Borges short story collections, <i>The Aleph</i> and <i>The Maker</i> (a.k.a. <i>Dreamtigers</i>), and also contains a small segment called <i>Museum</i> that contains two very small short fiction pieces. Overall this collection is a disappointment compared to <i>Ficciones</i>. The stories in <i>The Aleph</i> were mostly very strong; vintage Borges.<br/><br/>The stories in <i>The Maker</i> were all very short, many no more than a single page, but aside from the occasional masterpiece I found them mostly pedestria</span>
  <span id="freeText4701176504770431021" style="display:none"><i>The Aleph and Other Stories</i> collects two Borges short story collections, <i>The Aleph</i> and <i>The Maker</i> (a.k.a. <i>Dreamtigers</i>), and also contains a small segment called <i>Museum</i> that contains two very small short fiction pieces. Overall this collection is a disappointment compared to <i>Ficciones</i>. The stories in <i>The Aleph</i> were mostly very strong; vintage Borges.<br /><br />The stories in <i>The Maker</i> were all very short, many no more than a single page, but aside from the occasional masterpiece I found them mostly pedestrian, boring, and overall somewhat pointless. Some of them read like half-baked ideas that were floating around in Borges' head and that he decided to write down, others like the embryos of stories that never fully came to fruition.<br /><br />The segment titled <i>Museum</i> was awful and didn't seem to fit in with the collective whole of the book at all; they should have finished this collection after <i>The Maker</i> in my opinion. My cumulative rating for everything is 3.58 stars, but Goodreads doesn't offer half-star ratings, so I give this collection four stars. My individual ratings for each story, for each book/segment as a whole, and for the entire book as a whole are found below:<br /><br /><i>THE ALEPH <br /><br />The Immortal: 4/5<br />The Dead Man: 2.5/5<br />The Theologians: 3/5<br />Story of the Warrior and the Captive Maiden: 4/5<br />A Biography of Tadeo Isidoro Cruz: 4/5<br />Emma Zunz: 5/5<br />The House of Asterion: 5/5<br />The Other Death: 5/5<br />Deutsches Requiem: 5/5<br />Averroës' Search: 1/5<br />The Zahir: 5/5<br />The Writing of the God: 5/5<br />Ibn-Hakam al-Bokhari, Murdered in His Labyrinth: 4/5<br />The Two Kings and the Two Labyrinths: 5/5<br />The Wait: 5/5<br />The Man on the Threshold: 4/5<br />The Aleph: 2/5<br /><br />68.5/85 or 80.59% or 4.03 stars<br /><br />-------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />THE MAKER (A.K.A. DREAMTIGERS)<br /><br />The Maker: 4/5<br />Dreamtigers: 4/5<br />A Dialog About a Dialog: 2/5<br />Toenails: 3/5<br />Covered Mirrors: 4/5<br />Argumentum Ornithologicum: 1/5<br />The Captive: 5/5<br />The Mountebank: 3/5<br />Delia Elena San Marco: 4/5<br />A Dialog Between Dead Men: 4/5<br />The Plot: 2/5<br />A Problem: 2/5<br />The Yellow Rose: 2/5<br />The Witness: 5/5<br />Martin Fierro: 3/5<br />Mutations: 4/5<br />Parable of Cervantes and the Quixote: 2/5<br />Paradiso, XXXI, 108: 5/5<br />Parable of the Palace: 3/5<br />Everything and Nothing: 5/5<br />Ragnarök: 3/5<br />Inferno, I, 32: 5/5<br />Borges and I: 4/5<br /><br />79/115 or 68.70% or 3.44 stars<br /><br />-------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />MUSEUM<br /><br />On Exactitude in Science: 1/5<br />In Memoriam, J.F.K.: 2/5<br /><br />3/10 or 30% or 1.5 stars<br /><br />-------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />TOTAL CUMULATIVE SCORE<br /><br />150.5/210 or 71.67% or 3.58 stars</i></span>
